reviews.review: Entertaining but just not believable when every single break goes to the good guys...I prefer the Rogue One movie formula where the good guys win, but with real sacrifice.
Pandering to PC culture and "nostalgia" at the expense of a good story. They must think all Star Wars fans are blindly devoted and devoid of thought. Maybe most are? Not this one.

Tries to do to much and rushes from plot device to plot device. Very apparent that they were trying to rewrite and forget TLJ. This movie suffers from poor storytelling and seems to really highlight that this new set of star wars films have been made up as they go along. Hard pass on this one
This was the only way this could have ended and been satisfying at tying up the whole saga

I didn't honestly think JJ was capable of delivering this fine of a film. His films and tv shows have always felt very safe and divested of emotion. This is a tour de force and a magnificent end to what has amounted to nearly 43 years of my life. Easily the best picture in the series since Jedi, even bettering rogue one, which I thought was a really good film. I am so happy with what JJ has done here and I will be forever grateful he embraced the world of star wars, including us super fans and gave us such a loving sendoff. especially after the spit in the face that TLJ was. Dear Rian: please watch ROS and learn what it means to be at the helm of something truly loved. There is a powerful lesson to be learned.
Movie critics always seem to be looking for some agenda, this fixed everything Rian Johnson tried to do with the franchise.

I thought this movie was one of the best of the franchise.  Edge of the seat the entire time.  Seemed like it went back to its roots and everyone in the theater clapped at the end.  All of my die hard friends said the same thing.  "Great end to the story line".

Enjoyed it alot. Had it issues but most of those seemed to have been from trying to repair the damage caused by the last jedi. Lots of Easter eggs, great fight scenes. Pretty obvious direction for Rey but enjoyable none the less. C3PO stole the show with the 1 liners.

Truly embarrassing. For all those that are giving this 5 stars... a perfect rating?!? Are you serious? You have to be paid shills or just willfully ignorant. This film is a disaster. The fact that they had to bring Palpatine back to try and salvage this was sad enough. Couple that with the cringe writing, frantic pace, and completely nonsensical plot, and you have a real mess on your hands. This was difficult to sit through and watch until the end. This film completes the dismantling of the original trilogy in such a disrespectful way. They are actually destroying source content... what a joke. None of this is canon.
